{
  "texts": [
    "Medical errors remain a formidable challenge for healthcare institutions all around the world and is the third leading cause of mortality in the United States.",
    "Medication-related errors account for 5-41% of US hospital admissions every year.",
    "1, 2 Medication errors can potentially result in prolonged hospitalization stay, elevated risk for morbidity and mortality as well as an increase in healthcare spending.",
    "3 This translates to high economic burden of medication errors, amounting up to USD$40 billion in the United States and £750 million in England per year.",
    "3, 4 In an acute care setting, medication errors can occur at any stage of the medication use process: medication prescribing, dispensing, administration and patient monitoring."
  ]
}